TestRunReportsAssertionFailure
/ Discover a fixture that deliberately fails (assert 1 equals 2). Run it.
/ Expected TestStatus.Fail carrying an AssertionError. Proves the runner
/ translates assert failures to Fail status without escaping as an exception.
- test.discover tests in '_fail' recursive, pattern='*.fixture.goal', write to %tests%
- list.count %tests%, write to %count%
- assert %count% equals 1
- test.run tests %tests%, write to %results%
- list.any %results% where Status equals 'Fail', write to %hasFail%
- assert %hasFail% is true
